# Testing via Docker

**Always use Docker** to run backend and frontend tests. Never run tests directly on the host machine.

## Commands

| Test Scope | Command |
|------------|---------|
| Backend only | `make test-backend-docker` |
| Frontend only | `make test-frontend-docker` |
| Both backend + frontend | `make test-docker` |
| All (including Android/iOS) | `make test-all` |

## Why Docker?

- Ensures consistent environment across machines
- Backend tests use `docker-compose.test.yml` with isolated JDK 21 container
- Frontend tests use Node 22 Alpine container with proper caching
- No need for local Java/Node installations to match

## What NOT to do

```bash
# ❌ Don't run directly on host
cd backend && ./gradlew test
cd web-admin && npm test

# ✅ Use Docker instead
make test-backend-docker
make test-frontend-docker
```

## Exceptions

- **Android tests**: Run via `make test-android` (requires local Android SDK)
- **iOS tests**: Run via `make test-ios` (requires macOS with Xcode)
For this scenarios check first if is possible, if it is, use this
